A program that works in different modes to implement the services
concept of Kuberentes

div.style: text-align: left;

ul.li:
Mode 1: Iptables, on the basis of service spec it modify
the host iptables.
Mode 2: Ipvs, used when ip-tables are not supported on sytem

div.span: A program that actually creates & runs containers on the host

div.style: text-align: left;

ul.li:
Containerd talks to runc to actually run containers on the worker
node

Technically, runc is an low level container runtime that
implements the OCI (open container initiative) spec

So the flow of the container creation is like this
api-server -> kubelet -> containerd -> runc
